. La tercera jornada describe con gran detallismo, casi periodístico, el ceremonial del duelo con todos los elementos y partes que componían ese acto, tomados de la narración de fray Prudencio de Sandoval.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Spanish, Castilian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh1 aCalderón de la Barca, Pedro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoncero López, Victoriano, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z978311131826408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertVervuert Complete eBook-Package 2023z9783110998719oZDB-207-IBV40uhttps://doi.org/10.31819/978396869430640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783968694306423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783968694306/original  a978-3-11-131826-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023b2023  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-207-IBVb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023